# pi agent-board runtime state — never manage these (rosters, views, sessions,
# launch-prefs, per-project boards created by the `pi` wrapper). They are
# regenerated at runtime and would constantly drift / get clobbered by apply.
.pi/agent/agent-board
.pi/agent/boards

# Repo meta-docs — these are the dotfiles repo's own guide/readme, NOT dotfiles.
# Anchored with a leading slash so they only match the repo root and never the
# legitimate, deployed .pi/agent/AGENTS.md or .claude/CLAUDE.md. Without this,
# they land at ~/AGENTS.md and ~/CLAUDE.md and pollute the agent context of
# every project under ~.
/AGENTS.md
/CLAUDE.md
/README.md
/screenshot*.png
